CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: A strong body with a dense coat of hair swarming with bloodthirsty parasites.

Description.LocalizedString: A long, traditional dress made of linen with large floral embroidery, decorated with natural motifs.
Made from many pelts, and patched with many more. Provides surprising levels of warmth.
Each morning, she hunted and brought back game ranging from rodents to vultures, all to be sacrificed.
The tattered uniform of a Cossack soldier who fought bravely against Anna and paid the ultimate price.
Alerted by a howl in the moonless night, she hunted trespassers and tore them into pieces.
Her clothing, burnt to shreds, provided little protection from the fire. The pain was seared into her skin.
Intricate garb of the fabrics stitched from the clothes of her victims.
All that was important to her was that the dress stayed out of her way while she hunted.
Nothing could hurt her when she wore this impregnable armor.
Nothing in any realm could hurt her when she wore this impregnable armor.

Description.LocalizedString: Death first… Sentence afterwards!
She brought her beloved dolls along with her.

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: A heavy winter coat lined with the skins of captured prey. Provides sufficient warmth even in the deepest of winters.
This light garb is not meant for long periods in the harsh wilderness. Curl up and take refuge from the cold winds in front of the fireplace.

Description.LocalizedString: Look children! Toys for you to admire!

A crown emanating a festive and ominous aura created by The Entity’s biggest fan.

A crown crafted for a very special anniversary.
“Thank you for supporting & inspiring us along the years!” —The Dead by Daylight Team

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: Coarse bloody feathers to adorn your mask. The bird’s skull painting your cheeks red, your faces as one. It’s the beauty of the fittest.
A thick film of yellow serum drips from the dark lashes of her eyes.

Description.LocalizedString: A brown-haired, muddy boar head with long, sharp tusks. Ideal to crush your opponent.
A way to commemorate the decapitation of a terrified animal.
The bloody remains of the reindeer she decapitated on the first night.
A macabre mask whose original purpose of design is unknown. It seemed a fitting visage for Anna as she massacred German cavalry units.
After desperation turned her to cannibalism, her flesh melted away, horns adorned her head and she became the monster that her hunger drove her to be.
Under the mask was pain, confusion, and fear.
Two faces as one, embodying the paradoxical identity of villain and provider.
A mask they found themselves wearing at the masquerade ball.
Her starfish hairpin and floating blue veil make her feel like the little girl living by the sea.
At night, you might mistake her for a wild animal in the forest.
In the darkness of the Trials, you might mistake her for a beast hiding in trees.

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: A powerful symbol for evening rituals as the seasons change.
A powerful symbol for evening rituals as the seasons change.

Description.LocalizedString: Now the Red Queen will give you options: The ax or the ax, and don’t twiddle your thumbs about it.
A new mask made of leftovers.

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: Come child, don't cry. Be good for your kitty momma.

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: Let the fear of death and disgust wash over you; your quarry will feel it even more so. That is when you strike!

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: Some dry rot spreads to the head of the axe where the serum leaks, soaking the broad blade in a putrid smell.

Description.LocalizedString: A ragged battle axe strapped with a boar’s sharp canines, powerful tusks, and hard hoofed toes.
It may be handmade, but it is perfectly balanced and razor-sharp. Good for hunting all manner of game.
She bound animal parts to her hatchets, smeared with sacrificial blood.
A weapon that's proven itself in the chaos of war, this hatchet holds the dog tag of its deceased owner around its hilt.
She dipped the flesh-adorned weapon into the blood of those who did not respect the Mordeo’s ritual.
The heat of the flames deformed the steel head, giving it an unsettling, mottled look.
The harrowing, artful blade she used to extract judgment.
A perfect gift to throw at survivors during the holiday season.
A primitive weapon used to cut wood and, in her case, people's heads.
An axe permeated with old, gloomy stories about the Red Forest.
An axe permeated with old, gloomy stories about the Lost Realms.
An axe with a serrated blade for maximum damage.
An axe with a serrated blade for maximum damage.

Description.LocalizedString: Off with your head!
The blades were unbreakable.
A disturbing rabbit’s face was attached at the end of the axe.
A serrated blade for a tangy swing.
